(33, 1, '2023-06-18 13:58:02', '2023-06-18 09:58:02', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":40,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/tem/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Van_Gogh_-_Starry_Night_-_Google_Art_Project-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-40\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Starry Night\" is one of the most famous and recognized paintings in the world, created by the Dutch post-impressionist artist Vincent van Gogh. Completed in 1889, it is known for its vibrant colors, expressive brushwork, and the iconic depiction of a swirling night sky.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Van Gogh painted \"Starry Night\" during his stay at the Saint-Paul-de-Mausole asylum in Saint-Rmy-de-Provence, France. It was a period of intense creativity for him, and despite his struggles with mental health, he produced many notable works during this time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The painting depicts a small village, dominated by a cypress tree, against the backdrop of a tumultuous night sky. The sky is filled with swirling clouds and bright stars, including a crescent moon. The stars radiate light and seem to move dynamically across the canvas, creating a sense of movement and energy. The brushstrokes are thick and bold, adding texture and depth to the painting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The choice of colors in \"Starry Night\" is characteristic of van Gogh\'s unique style. He used intense blues and yellows to represent the night and the moon, contrasting with the warm earth tones of the village and the tree. This combination of colors creates a vibrant and expressive atmosphere, evoking a sense of both tranquility and turbulence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Starry Night\" is not a literal representation of the night sky but rather a symbolic and emotional interpretation. Van Gogh sought to convey his own inner emotions and experiences through his art, and this painting is considered a reflection of his inner turmoil and longing for serenity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Today, \"Starry Night\" is housed in the collection of the Museum of Modern Art (MoMA) in New York City, where it continues to captivate and inspire millions of visitors. It has become an iconic image in popular culture and has had a profound influence on the art world, making it one of the most celebrated and enduring works of art in history.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '\"Starry night\"', '\"Starry night\" by Vincent van Gogh', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'starry-night', '', '', '2023-06-18 13:58:02', '2023-06-18 09:58:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/tem/?p=33', 0, 'post', '', 0),
