(41, 1, '2023-06-18 13:58:02', '2023-06-18 09:58:02', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":40,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/tem/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Van_Gogh_-_Starry_Night_-_Google_Art_Project-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-40\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Starry Night\" is one of the most famous and recognized paintings in the world, created by the Dutch post-impressionist artist Vincent van Gogh. Completed in 1889, it is known for its vibrant colors, expressive brushwork, and the iconic depiction of a swirling night sky.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Van Gogh painted \"Starry Night\" during his stay at the Saint-Paul-de-Mausole asylum in Saint-Rmy-de-Provence, France. It was a period of intense creativity for him, and despite his struggles with mental health, he produced many notable works during this time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The painting depicts a small village, dominated by a cypress tree, against the backdrop of a tumultuous night sky. The sky is filled with swirling clouds and bright stars, including a crescent moon. The stars radiate light and seem to move dynamically across the canvas, creating a sense of movement and energy. The brushstrokes are thick and bold, adding texture and depth to the painting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The choice of colors in \"Starry Night\" is characteristic of van Gogh\'s unique style. He used intense blues and yellows to represent the night and the moon, contrasting with the warm earth tones of the village and the tree. This combination of colors creates a vibrant and expressive atmosphere, evoking a sense of both tranquility and turbulence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Starry Night\" is not a literal representation of the night sky but rather a symbolic and emotional interpretation. Van Gogh sought to convey his own inner emotions and experiences through his art, and this painting is considered a reflection of his inner turmoil and longing for serenity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Today, \"Starry Night\" is housed in the collection of the Museum of Modern Art (MoMA) in New York City, where it continues to captivate and inspire millions of visitors. It has become an iconic image in popular culture and has had a profound influence on the art world, making it one of the most celebrated and enduring works of art in history.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '\"Starry night\"', '\"Starry night\" by Vincent van Gogh', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '33-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-06-18 13:58:02', '2023-06-18 09:58:02', '', 33, 'http://localhost:8888/tem/?p=41', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(42, 1, '2023-06-18 14:00:47', '2023-06-18 10:00:47', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":43,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/tem/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Vincent_Willem_van_Gogh_127-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-43\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>\"Sunflowers\" is a series of still-life paintings created by Vincent van Gogh between 1888 and 1889. Van Gogh\'s fascination with sunflowers began in Paris, where he encountered Japanese ukiyo-e woodblock prints, which often featured vibrant and stylized depictions of flowers. Inspired by these prints, van Gogh decided to create a series of paintings focusing on sunflowers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The series consists of several variations of sunflower bouquets, typically depicted in a vase. Van Gogh experimented with different compositions, colors, and arrangements, capturing the beauty and vitality of the sunflowers in his own distinctive style.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the most well-known paintings from the series is simply titled \"Sunflowers\" or \"Vase with Fifteen Sunflowers.\" It features a bouquet of fifteen sunflowers in a yellow vase against a yellow background. Van Gogh used bold, expressive brushstrokes and vibrant colors, emphasizing the textured petals and the play of light on the flowers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The sunflowers in van Gogh\'s paintings are not just decorative elements; they hold symbolic significance for the artist. He considered them to be a representation of happiness, friendship, and the beauty of nature. Van Gogh once wrote to his brother Theo, \"The sunflower is mine, in a way.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The \"Sunflowers\" series is notable for its vivid use of color and the textured application of paint. Van Gogh used thick brushstrokes and layering techniques to create a three-dimensional effect, giving the paintings a sense of depth and movement. The intense yellows, oranges, and greens contribute to the energetic and expressive quality of the works.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Sunflowers\" has become one of van Gogh\'s most recognized and celebrated series, and the paintings are housed in various museums around the world. They are admired for their boldness, emotional intensity, and their ability to evoke a sense of joy and optimism.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Van Gogh\'s \"Sunflowers\" series represents his unique artistic vision and his ability to infuse ordinary objects with profound meaning and beauty. The paintings continue to captivate art enthusiasts and serve as a testament to the enduring legacy of van Gogh as one of the most influential artists in history.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '\"Sunflowers\"', '\"Sunflowers\" or \"Vase with Fifteen Sunflowers\"  by Vincet van Gogh.\n Van Gogh once wrote to his brother Theo, \"The sunflower is mine, in a way.\"', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sunflowers', '', '', '2023-06-18 14:01:23', '2023-06-18 10:01:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/tem/?p=42', 0, 'post', '', 0),
