(85, 1, '2023-06-22 18:57:19', '2023-06-22 14:57:19', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Vincent van Gogh had a complicated relationship with women throughout his life, but he did not have any wives. However, there were two significant women in his life who played important roles.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"width\":241,\"height\":317,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"\" width=\"241\" height=\"317\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of them was his sister, Anna van Gogh. Vincent had a close bond with his sister, and they maintained a strong relationship through correspondence. Anna supported Vincent emotionally and financially throughout his artistic career, often providing him with encouragement and stability during challenging times. She was a source of comfort and understanding for Vincent, and their letters provide valuable insights into his thoughts and artistic pursuits.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"width\":362,\"height\":423,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-0njC0A_m574/UvPMDoYqUhI/AAAAAAAA4-E/GM-zJ0qEbao/s1600/Margot-Begemann.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"362\" height=\"423\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The other significant woman in van Gogh\'s life was Margot Begemann. Margot was a young woman whom van Gogh fell in love with while living in The Hague. They had a passionate and turbulent relationship, but unfortunately, it ended in tragedy. Margot\'s father disapproved of their relationship, and their difficulties, combined with van Gogh\'s emotional instability, led to their separation. Distraught over the breakup, van Gogh experienced a mental breakdown and cut off part of his ear. This incident marked a turning point in his life and artistic career.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Although Vincent van Gogh did not have a wife, his relationships with women, particularly his sister Anna and Margot Begemann, had a significant impact on his personal life and artistic development. These connections shaped his emotional experiences and influenced the themes and intensity of his artwork.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Women in van Gogh\'s life', 'Women in van Gogh\'s life\nVincent van Gogh had a complicated relationship with women throughout his life, but he did not have any wives. However, there were two significant women in his life who played important roles.\n Anna van Gogh\n Margot Begemann', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'women-in-van-goghs-life', '', '', '2023-06-22 18:57:19', '2023-06-22 14:57:19', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/tem/?p=85', 0, 'post', '', 0),
